      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FOR ALWAYS ARDEN NZ (1) has had a month off since breaking in the G3 Golden Guitar Final but led from wider than this to win a heat of that series prior. Has recorded a win and placing from two attempts at this circuit and distance and possesses the speed to take full advantage of the ace draw. MR TEDDY NZ (9) turned in a strong performance last start when he battled on bravely to be beaten less then 2m into second at Menangle. No favours expected from this draw but came from a wide barrier for a Bathurst win three back. Player with even luck. BABY YOUR THE ONE (7) draws for a trail and could be dangerous if she gets the gaps. I BET YOU (3) was good in second after racing parked last start. Draws well so could go one better.",
